Logging Subsystem 5.5.16 - Red Hat OpenShift

Red Hat Product Security has rated this update as having a security impact of Moderate. A Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE link(s) in the References section.
notes.title: Topic

notes.text:
Logging Subsystem 5.5.16 - Red Hat OpenShift

Security Fix(es):

* openshift-logging: LokiStack authorisation is cached too broadly (CVE-2023-4456)

For more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.

acknowledgments.summary: This issue was discovered by Red Hat.

notes.text: A flaw was found in openshift-logging LokiStack. The key used for caching is just the token, which is too broad. This issue allows a user with a token valid for one action to execute other actions as long as the authorization allowing the original action is still cached.
notes.title: Vulnerability description

notes.text: openshift-logging: LokiStack authorisation is cached too broadly
